381
00:28:10,452 --> 00:28:11,952
Then why not?

382
00:28:11,952 --> 00:28:15,212
You are so good. You can't be wronged.

383
00:28:15,912 --> 00:28:22,712
Dad, do you believe in fate, coincidence?

384
00:28:23,352 --> 00:28:25,252
Of course.

385
00:28:25,252 --> 00:28:28,072
I have experience in this.

386
00:28:28,072 --> 00:28:32,592
Your mom and I wouldn't be together if there's no coincidence.

387
00:28:32,592 --> 00:28:35,472
- I used to drive a truck, you know. 
 - Yes.

388
00:28:35,472 --> 00:28:39,712
Long, long ago, I was making deliveries in my truck.

389
00:28:39,712 --> 00:28:42,892
A girl stopped me and said she wanted me to give her a ride.

390
00:28:42,892 --> 00:28:47,852
I was kind and nice, so I gave her a ride.

391
00:28:47,852 --> 00:28:50,412
I thought you did it because she's pretty.

392
00:28:50,412 --> 00:28:53,092
Definitely, right?

393
00:28:53,092 --> 00:28:56,312
We had a good chat.

394
00:28:56,312 --> 00:28:59,172
But everything has to come to an end. When we arrived, she left.

395
00:28:59,172 --> 00:29:03,092
You didn't even get her contact? What a pity.

396
00:29:03,092 --> 00:29:06,132
Indeed. I was upset for several days.  I didn't even eat well.

397
00:29:06,132 --> 00:29:08,672
- That upset? 
 - But as the old saying goes,

398
00:29:08,672 --> 00:29:11,972
every cloud has a silver lining.

399
00:29:11,972 --> 00:29:17,172
Another day, long, long ago, I went to eat at a restaurant.

400
00:29:18,372 --> 00:29:22,172
- Guess who I met? 
 - The girl who stopped your truck.

401
00:29:22,172 --> 00:29:24,632
H-How did you know? Did I ever tell you this?

402
00:29:24,632 --> 00:29:28,532
You never told me. That sounds like those soap operas.

403
00:29:28,532 --> 00:29:33,632
No, this is fate.

404
00:29:33,632 --> 00:29:39,352
I ordered a bowl of rice and she gave me a bowl of soup.

405
00:29:39,352 --> 00:29:41,392
